entry.title: ClientResourceProvider Main Thread Callbacks
entry.content:
Currently a lot of the ReleaseCallbacks for resources PostTask from the

Impl thread back to the Main thread.



This causes contention, since they are all separate jumps.



This also means that we are not sure when they are actually done being

processed, so we are unable to properly flush the context. We currently

can try to use a delayed flush, but that's racy.



This change adds a Main-Thread ReleaseCallback option. With this, once

resources are Returned from the Viz DisplayCompositor, we can collect

the callbacks for Main, and batch them together in one jump. While also

jumping back once they are done. Thus allowing us to run a flush in a

known state.



TEST=ClientResourceProviderTest.EvictionNotifiesMainAndFlushes

Chrome memory.infra tracing also confirms Canvas resource being

flushed and no more GPU Shared Image allocation for it.

entry.title: [CSC] Sends main frame's innerHTML to companion side panel
entry.content:
Captures the innerHTML of the main frame using the API introduced in

b/304353698.



Since we cannot easily tell whether the page has finished loading by

the time CSC UI is ready (i.e., sends loading started signal), we attempt

to capture the innertHTML both when the CSC UI is ready and also on

WebContentObserver::DidFinishNavigation(). However we don't send it to

the CSC UI until it is ready.



Note that these events may happen in any order. If the CSC UI is ready

before DidFinishNavigation(), the innerHTML can be sent to the CSC UI

twice; with potentially more complete content the second time. It is

also possiblethat DidFinishNavigation() is never called if the CSC side

panel is openedon an already loaded page or if the page is loaded from

in-memory cache.



This CL also fixes a bug for capturing the page title where the title

was not being sent to the CSC UI if DidFinishNavigation() was not called.



Bug: b/298449509, 1511189

entry.title: Add test support for color providers in Blink::Page
entry.content:
This CL adds test support for the color provders that exist in

Blink::Page. The color providers were introduced in this CL:4898493.

Color providers will be used for painting and as such it is important

to make sure they are not null even in tests.



The CL implements a MockColorProviderSource class in render_view_test.cc,

which simulates the color provider source that is normally provided by

the browser process. The GetRendererColorMap method is used to set the

color_provider_colors view param, which is used by the renderer process

to create the color providers.



The CL also adds a utility function, CreateColorProviderForBlinkTests,

in color_provider_utils.h, which helps create color providers in

blink tests that do not use IPC. The function is called in

DummyPageHolder() and frame_test_helpers::WebViewHelper to ensure that

the color providers are not null even in tests.

behavior. This is a no-op, and just a simple naming change for the function.

window by default, leading to failed tests where this function
